| `stylePosition` | `React.CSSProperties` | No | The optional styles applied to the position node wrapped around the root node. |
| `title` | `string` | No | A Tooltip title. |
| `tooltipOffsetSkidding` | `number` | No | Cross-axis pixel offset of the tooltip. |
| `tooltipOffsetDistance` | `number` | No | Main-axis pixel offset of the tooltip. |
| `delayOpen` | `boolean` | No | Whether to delay showing the tooltip. |
| `delayOpenDuration` | `number` | No | Time in milliseconds before tooltip shows when `delayOpen` is true. |
| `event` | `ReactEvent) => void` | Yes | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface TooltipProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /**
   * Defines where tooltip should align relative to its target element.
   * NOTE: horizontal alignments cannot be paired with horizontal positions.
   * NOTE: Alignment will also be ignored when position is set to left or right
   *
   * @default 'left'
   */
  alignment: Alignments;
  /** autoFocus: focus on Tooltip when it is opened */
  autoFocus?: boolean;
  /**
   * Allows easier access to elements while running functional tests. Renders
   * as a data-automation-id attribute on the mounted Tooltip div. Defaults to tooltip.
   */
  automationId?: string;
  /**
   * containerRef: callback that returns the ref for Tooltip container.
   *
   * @default () => undefined
   */
  containerRef: (ref: HTMLDivElement | null) => void;
  /** Disable response to focus events. */
  disableFocusListener?: boolean;
  /** Disable response to hover events. */
  disableHoverListener?: boolean;
  /** Disable response to click events. */
  disableClickListener?: boolean;
  /** Disable response to touch events. */
  disableTouchListener?: boolean;
  /** If true, a 'X' close icon will appear by Tooltip to allow user to close (dismiss). Defaults to false. */
  dismissible?: boolean;
  /**
   * Time in milliseconds before Tooltip will start to dismiss after trigger event fires.
   *
   * @default 0
   */
  duration: number;
  /**
   * Enable close event on click away.
   * enableClickAway does not work well when using focus or tabindex="0"
   * When the user recieves keyboard focus on to the next element the focus is lost and hence enableClickAway isn't valid anymore, please use Infolink for this use case.
   *
   * @default false
   */
  enableClickAway: boolean;
  /** The inner content of the Tooltip. */
  message?: string | React.ReactElement;
  /**
   * Positions tooltip from right or left of target selector
   *
   * @default 0
   * @deprecated Please use tooltipOffsetSkidding instead
   */
  offsetX: number;
  /**
   * Positions tooltip from top or bottom of target selector
   *
   * @default 0
   * @deprecated Please use tooltipOffsetDistance instead
   */
  offsetY: number;
  /** Handler that's fired when close icon ('X') is clicked. Tooltip will still close by default if this is supplied. */
  onClose?: ReactEventHandler;
  /** Handle that is fired when any keydown event fire on close icon control in tooltip. */
  onCloseButtonKeyDown?: React.KeyboardEventHandler;
  /** Handler that's fired when any keydown event fire on Tooltip content. */
  onKeyDown?: React.KeyboardEventHandler;
  /** Called when tooltip opened. */
  onShow?: ReactEventHandler;
  /** Whether to show the tooltip */
  open?: boolean;
  /**
   * Defines where tooltip should appear relative to its target elements.
   * If nothing specified, it will attempt to automatically position
   * the tooltip where space is available.
   *
   * @default 'top'
   */
  position: Positions;
  /** preventOverflow: an object variable; used to prevent Tooltip from being positioned outside the boundary. */
  preventOverflow?: PreventOverflow;
  /** The optional styles applied to the position node wrapped around the root node. */
  stylePosition?: React.CSSProperties;
  /** A Tooltip title. */
  title?: string;
  /**
   * tooltipOffsetSkidding: the cross-axis pixel distance that the popup should be offset from targetElement
   *
   * @default 0
   */
  tooltipOffsetSkidding: number;
  /**
   * tooltipOffsetDistance: the main-axis pixel distance that the popup should be offset from targetElement
   *
   * @default 0
   */
  tooltipOffsetDistance: number;
  /**
   * delayOpen: Whether to delay the open of tooltip or not
   *
   * @default false
   */
  delayOpen: boolean;
  /**
   * delayOpenDuration: Time in milliseconds before Tooltip shows after trigger event fires.
   *
   * @default 800
   */
  delayOpenDuration: number;
}

export type ReactEventHandler = (event: ReactEvent) => void;

export type ReactEvent =
  | React.MouseEvent
  | React.KeyboardEvent
  | React.TouchEvent
  | React.FocusEvent;
```

</details>

## Design Variants

The following variant axes control the component's visual appearance:

### Position → use prop `position`

- `Top left` **(default)**
- `Top middle`
- `Top right`
- `Right top`
- `Right middle`
- `Right bottom`
- `Bottom right`
- `Bottom middle`
- `Bottom left`
- `Left bottom`
- `Left middle`
- `Left top`

> **12 design variants** are defined in Figma. [View in Figma](https://www.figma.com/design/VO8rsMYDqsDY44J9yEVyES9Y?node-id=101939%3A2646&m=dev)

